  "texts": [
    "Individual device modeling provides the foundation for the consistent representation of large-scale network data.",
    "In particular, ontology-based approaches can be leveraged to represent entities.",
    "Using physical device information, environmental information, topological node information, network link information, container/virtual machine information, and network element configuration information, individual digital twin models can be developed for communication network devices and logical network elements.",
    "Functional modeling, tailored to the requirements of actual NFs, uses diverse functional modules throughout the lifecycle to achieve dynamic and evolving network reasoning and decision-making.",
    "These functional models can be constructed and expanded across multiple dimensions based on the needs of various network applications."
  ],
